        <section>
            <h2>
                Mission of TechCon 2024
            </h2>
            <p>
              To empower a global community of innovators, technologists, and changemakers by creating a platform that fosters knowledge-sharing, collaboration, and the responsible development of technology for a smarter, more inclusive, and sustainable future.
            </p>
            <h2>
                Notable Speakers from Previous TechCon Editions
            </h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Dr. Adaora Emefiele
                  <p>
                      A trailblazer in African AI development, Dr. Adaora is known for pioneering machine learning models adapted to local languages. Her work in ethical AI has influenced policy in several African countries. At TechCon, she delivered keynotes on “Bias in AI” and “Building Inclusive Algorithms.”
                  </p>
                  <figure>
                    <img src="./Assets/Dr Adaora Emefiele.png.jpg" alt="picture of Dr. Adaora Emefiele">
                    <figcaption>
                         CTO, NovaGen AI | Speaker at TechCon 2022 & 2023
                    </figcaption>
                  </figure>
                </li>

                <li>
                    Samuel Kentaro
                    <p>
                        A Japanese-Nigerian robotics engineer, Samuel’s innovations in smart agriculture have transformed small-scale farming across Asia and Africa. His session “AgroTech and the Rise of Smart Farming” drew over 1,000 attendees and inspired cross-border startup collaborations.
                    </p>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="./Assets/Samuel kentaro.png.jpg" alt="Image of samuel Kentaro">
                        <figcaption>
                             Founder & CEO, GreenByte Robotics | TechCon 2023
                        </figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    Tara Mensah
                    <p>
                          Tara is a digital transformation expert and one of the first women to lead a cloud-computing startup in West Africa. Her contributions to mobile-first enterprise tools have empowered thousands of SMEs. At TechCon 2022, she led a masterclass on “Cloud as a Catalyst for Economic Growth.”
                    </p>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="./Assets/Tera Mensah.jpg" alt="Image of Tara Mensah">
                        <figcaption>
                             Head of Product, NubiaCloud | TechCon 2022
                        </figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </li>

                <li>
                   Jacob Martinez

                    <p>
                       Jacob is a leading voice in virtual and augmented reality development. With over a decade at Meta, he contributed to the architecture of Horizon Worlds. At TechCon, he ran a demo and workshop on “The Future of Spatial Computing in Everyday Life.”
                    </p>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="./Assets/Jacob Martinez.png.jpg" alt="Image of Jacon Matinez">
                        <figcaption>
                             Lead Engineer, Meta XR Labs | TechCon 2023
                        </figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </li>
